Amira Gill (@amiragill) is a vocalist, songwriter, and music therapist from New Delhi. She has a degree in Music Therapy from Berklee College of Music, Boston. Her original music, written in English and Hindi, reflects some of her biggest influences - the rootedness of Indian Folk music and the abandon of Soul music.

latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Abhishek Gupta Benares
@abhishekguptabenares 

Growing up in Benares had a profound cultural and artistic impact on Abhishek Gupta and this collection embodies those aesthetic qualities. Using traditional handloom fabrics juxtaposed with fine appliqué, pleating, intricate thread  embroidery & fine quilting, each garment is a masterpiece with assiduous craftsmanship, impeccable cut and fine tailoring, finished to invisible detail.

latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Our bridal edit this season is all about celebrating the India Modern Bride and complementing her individuality. 

Using playful hues of reds, fuchsia and metallics, the latest collection is exquisitely constructed using the most luxurious fabrics and finishings.

With a strong focus on skill, craftsmanship and artistry, The Red Series fuses the use of gota, kundan with intricate techniques of kasheeda, kasab and zardozi, bringing drama to each of the pieces.
